# 🧠 Ontology — Systems Map

Sparse chrome, dense center. The viewport belongs to the force-directed network graph.

## 🎯 Vibe in One Line

> Research figure on warm paper. Muted earth-tone network. The graph IS the page.

## 🎨 Palette

| Role | Color | Notes |
|------|-------|-------|
| Page background | `#0A0A0A` → `#F5F0E8` | Dark chrome shell, cream content area |
| Card / graph container | `#FFFFFF` | Single large white card holds the network |
| Card shadow | `0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06)` | Soft |
| Card radius | `16px` | |
| Eyebrow label | `#DC143C` crimson | "ONTOLOGY" |
| Title text | `#1A1A1A` | |
| Node labels | `#111` / `rgba(0,0,0,0.84)` | On SVG |

### Edge Colors (d3 network)

| Relationship | Color | Meaning |
|-------------|-------|---------|
| Positive | `#4F7F63` | Muted green — "rise together" |
| Negative | `#B79A7A` | Muted brown — "trade off" |
| Lagged | `#A74D4D` | Muted red — "predicts" |

## 📐 Layout

- `content-width` centered column
- One big white card: `borderRadius: 16, padding: 24px 16px`
- Responsive SVG force graph fills the card
- Legend row below the graph
- Minimal header section above — just eyebrow + title

## 🔤 Typography

| Element | Font | Size | Weight | Style |
|---------|------|------|--------|-------|
| Eyebrow "ONTOLOGY" | Inter | 11px | 600 | uppercase, crimson, 0.15em tracking |
| Page title | Playfair Display | clamp(32px, 7vw, 44px) | 400 | italic |
| Node labels (SVG) | Inter | varies | — | On graph nodes |
| Loading/error states | Inter | 14px | 400 | centered, muted |

## ✅ Do

- Let the network graph dominate — minimal UI around it
- Use muted earth tones for edges (green/brown/red)
- Keep one single white card as the graph container
- Use the standard cream + crimson eyebrow/title header pattern

## 🚫 Don't

- Don't add heavy UI around the graph — sparse chrome is the point
- Don't use bright/saturated colors for edges — muted earth tones only
- Don't use nutrition palette (yellow/ocean/glass) here
- Don't make the card smaller than viewport width minus padding
